title: Grateful Dead Live at Buckeye Lake Music Center on 1988-06-25
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger-> Franklin's Tower, Box Of Rain, Sugaree*, Memphis Blues*, West L.A. Fadeaway, Cassidy, Deal

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime, Blow Away, Foolish Heart-> Terrapin Station, Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> E: Not Fade Away, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

*w/ Hornsby on accordian. Bruce Hornsby and the Range opened.

reviews.review_text: Fantastic show! But damn was it hot! It was approximately 103 degrees out at this show in 88.  Great scene and the concert was tremendous.  A lot of people left early due to heat exhaustion.

Summer fun with grass lots. Victim 3rd time played
Blow Away 2nd time played
Foolish 3rd time played
Hornsby first appearance with the Dead. 

Fun show. Fun Summer.
